                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/374: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                            type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-03T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 3, 1932—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 3—5:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. From <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>. Your 418 November 26, 2
                    p.m. to Paris. League Secretariat has been advised of views of American experts
                    regarding inclusion China member on Preparatory Commission and regarding <pb
                        facs="0961" n="841" xml:id="pg_841"/> their desire for some delay in fixing
                    actual date in January for next meeting. In view of necessity of prompt
                    notification of other members of Preparatory Commission would appreciate early
                    cabled advice regarding date. [<persName corresp="#p_DNH1"
                    >Davis</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
